cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on online social networks and their influence on viral marketing, which falls under the scope of social and information networks. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the viewing of video ads as a means of user activity, which falls under the scope of multimedia. 
3. cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) - The paper discusses the revenue generation and cost of influence propagation for OSN providers, which falls under the scope of social and economic networks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a two-phase framework for seed selection and develops bounds to measure the quality of the seed set, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses the interaction between advertisers, OSN providers, and users, which falls under the scope of multiagent systems.
